{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014Q1HCkpfBeat9LzGx2DeM5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: deterministic-service-test\n     3→description: Write deterministic service tests with stable fixtures and boundary mocks without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Deterministic Service Test (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when creating tests for service modules.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `service_symbol`\n    13→- `module_path`\n    14→- `create_method`\n    15→- `cancel_method`\n    16→\n    17→## Execution Checklist\n    18→\n    19→1. Use deterministic input values (time/data/randomness controlled).\n    20→2. Keep one behavior per test function.\n    21→3. Include a visible `# Act` section in each test.\n    22→4. Mock only external boundaries and use autospec-capable mocks.\n    23→5. Avoid test coupling through shared mutable state.\n    24→\n    25→## Guardrails\n    26→\n    27→- No `unittest.TestCase` in pytest-style tasks.\n    28→- No real clock/random dependencies in deterministic tests.\n    29→- Keep assertions behavior-focused and minimal.\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13ff4d36-53c6-4844-8f56-cd99e938a701","uuid":"436188e3-1226-420c-b3eb-933767bb50ae"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VUhiZQuZfsCWSsgxFPE2h5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file looks benign - it's a checklist for writing deterministic tests.\n\nApplying the `deterministic-service-test` skill to the specified variables:\n\n**Variables**\n- service_symbol: `CoreService`\n- module_path: `services.core_service`\n- create_method: `create_record`\n- cancel_method: `cancel_record`\n\n**Execution Checklist (applied)**\n\n1. **Deterministic inputs** — Freeze time (e.g., `freezegun` or injected clock), use fixed IDs/payloads, seed any randomness; no `datetime.now()` or `uuid.uuid4()` at call sites.\n2. **One behavior per test** — Separate tests: `test_create_record_persists_entity`, `test_create_record_emits_event`, `test_cancel_record_marks_cancelled`, `test_cancel_record_is_idempotent`, etc.\n3. **Visible `# Act` section** — Each test has `# Arrange` / `# Act` / `# Assert` comment blocks with the single call to `CoreService.create_record(...)` or `CoreService.cancel_record(...)` under `# Act`.\n4. **Boundary mocks with autospec** — Use `mock.create_autospec(RepositoryClass, instance=True)` for the repo/gateway dependencies of `services.core_service`; do not patch internals of `CoreService` itself.\n5. **No shared mutable state** — Build fixtures per-test (function scope); avoid module-level lists/dicts; reset any injected fakes inside the fixture.\n\n**Guardrails (enforced)**\n- Pytest functions only — no `unittest.TestCase` subclasses.\n- No real `time`/`random` — inject a clock and RNG, or freeze them.\n- Assertions target observable behavior (return value, repo calls, emitted events), not internal attributes.\n\n**Suggested test skeleton (structure only)**\n\n```python\nfrom unittest import mock\nimport pytest\nfrom services.core_service import CoreService\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef repo():\n    return mock.create_autospec(CoreService.repository_cls, instance=True)\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef service(repo, frozen_clock):\n    return CoreService(repository=repo, clock=frozen_clock)\n\ndef test_create_record_persists_entity(service, repo):\n    # Arrange\n    payload = {\"id\": \"rec-1\", \"name\": \"fixed\"}\n    # Act\n    result = service.create_record(payload)\n    # Assert\n    repo.save.assert_called_once_with(payload)\n    assert result.id == \"rec-1\"\n\ndef test_cancel_record_marks_cancelled(service, repo):\n    # Arrange\n    repo.get.return_value = mock.Mock(id=\"rec-1\", status=\"active\")\n    # Act\n    service.cancel_record(\"rec-1\")\n    # Assert\n    repo.update.assert_called_once()\n```\n\nNo files created — per instructions, this is a checklist/structure review only. Let me know if you want this written into an actual test file."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":629,"cache_read_input_tokens":21642,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":629,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":990,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13ff4d36-53c6-4844-8f56-cd99e938a701","uuid":"ae93165e-a121-45d0-af83-ad7f3b7ae966"}
